.TH "drm_flip_work_commit" 9 "drm_flip_work_commit" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_flip_work_commit \- commit queued work
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_flip_work_commit
.BI "(struct drm_flip_work *work "  ","
.BI "struct workqueue_struct *wq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "work" 12
the flip-work
.IP "wq" 12
the work-queue to run the queued work on
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Trigger work previously queued by \fBdrm_flip_work_queue\fP to run
on a workqueue.  The typical usage would be to queue work (via
\fBdrm_flip_work_queue\fP) at any point (from vblank irq and/or
prior), and then from vblank irq commit the queued work.
